South Africa’s Empowerment Fund  to Raise $1.5 Billion, Business Day Says

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-04-08T06:00:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/south-africa-s-empowerment-fund-to-raise-1-5-billion-business-day-says.html
South Africa ’s National Empowerment
Fund plans to raise 10 billion rand of capital to fund five
projects, Business Day reported, citing Chief Executive Officer
Philisiwe Buthelezi.  The company has 15 projects worth 27 billion rand planned,
which form part of the government’s plan to create jobs, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper said today.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
